Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as 25b54dba775b31021a3a4677eb79e9771bcb97f7
nice, this looks a lot cleaner than the previous code. I am good with the changes made. just a small comment.
is this change intentional ?

Yes.  Because we now explicitly have the constexpr ifs match (and it's a compile failure to have a mismatch) we need to comment this back in.

Frankly, we commented this out, and it didn't really have the result we were looking for (a stronger push to get the backend merged into upstream).  We need to reevalute nbdproxy outside of this patch.

Can we do this in a different commit? 
I don't think this change belongs here

> Can we do this in a different commit?

Functionally, they're not separate.  I can put it in a predecessor commit to this one if you just want the git history to be separate, but if we start enforcing meson_options correctness (Which is a good thing) it also means.... they have to be correct.

Given that the NBD server is at least in review, I'm not sure this belongs commented out anyway.
ok, I figured out a way to do it.  It defeats the purpose of being consistent, but sets this option to false always in the bmcweb_config.h.

> git history to be separate

Yeah, git history separate but it is also I feel a separate discussion/change so yes. Thank you keeping it the same
FWIW, https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/69333 I suspect will clean it up by consolidating the two options into one.
Seems reasonable.
Always setting to false. Got it.
I think a bad merge conflict here
yep.  Removed.

Honest question.  Is the namespace a good idea?

BMCWEB_DO_OPTION

versus

bmcweb::DO_OPTION

I kinda wonder if the former would be better.
I don't have much of a preference, but I think BMCWEB_DO_OPTION is slightly better (easier to search and simpler)
I kinda think so too.  let me make that change.
Looks good to me as well. But this needs a rebase.
did these mean to get switched?

Yep, note that the option went from "bmcweb enable tls" to "bmcweb ... disable TLS"

This is one of the places where we inverted the option in meson.  Now that we're consistent, we have to keep the same "disabled" through the whole path.
Done
This doesn't look correct
Yep, two patches added that header here.  Fixed.
